commentary.p:
 (This is similar to the
    solution to .)  Let T(u,v)
    denote the matrix \twotwo{u}{v}{-v^\ast}{u^\ast}
      in {\mathcal M}_\Quat. We have the following.

	  T(u,v)+T(r,s)\amp = \twotwo{u}{v}{-v^\ast}{u^\ast} + \twotwo{r}{s}{-s^\ast}{r^\ast} 

	  \amp = \twotwo{u+r}{v+s}{-(v+s)^\ast}{(u+r)^\ast}

	  \amp = T(u+r,v+s)
	  T(u,v)T(r,s)\amp = \twotwo{u}{v}{-v^\ast}{u^\ast}  \twotwo{r}{s}{-s^\ast}{r^\ast} 

	  \amp = \twotwo{ur-vs^\ast}{us+vr^\ast}{-(us+vr^\ast)^\ast}{(ur-vs^\ast)^\ast}

	  \amp = T(ur-vs^\ast,us+vr^\ast)

statement.p:
Show that the
            following hold for all r,s\in U(\Quat).


R_r\circ R_s = R_{rs}

(R_r)^{-1}=R_{r^\ast}
